## When to Spawn Researchers

### Skip research (do it yourself) when:
- Request is straightforward, you understand the domain
- Sufficient context already in the bead description
- Similar work done before (check past PRDs in `docs/prds/`)
- Quick answer (< 10 minutes of reading/thinking)

### Spawn researchers when:
- Need competitive analysis (multiple competitors to investigate)
- Unfamiliar technology (need to research docs, best practices, ecosystem)
- Need to validate technical feasibility (library compatibility, performance, etc.)
- Multiple independent research questions
- Deep reading required (documentation, RFCs, academic papers)

**Rule of thumb**: If you can answer it in 10 minutes, do it yourself. If it needs deep reading or multiple sources, spawn researcher(s).

