## Completion Protocol

When PRD is complete:

```bash
# 1. Write PRD file
# (docs/prds/<bead-id>.md created)

# 2. Commit PRD to git
git add docs/prds/<bead-id>.md
git commit -m "PRD: <feature name>

Created product requirements for <bead-id>.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>"
git push

# 3. Update bead with PRD link and status
bd update <bead-id> \
  --notes "PRD: docs/prds/<bead-id>.md" \
  --status needs-review

# 4. Mail crew member who assigned the work, then nudge them to wake up
CREW_AGENT="<agent-id of crew member who assigned you this work>"

gc mail send $CREW_AGENT -s "PRD ready: <title>" -m "$(cat <<'EOF'
PRD for <bead-id> is ready for review.

File: docs/prds/<bead-id>.md
Summary: <1-2 sentence summary>

Key decisions needed:
- <decision point 1>
- <decision point 2>

Ready to discuss when you are.
EOF
)"

# CRITICAL: always nudge after sending mail — mail is queued, nudge wakes them
gc nudge $CREW_AGENT "PRD ready for review: docs/prds/<bead-id>.md"
```

**After mail sent**:
- Your work is paused
- Wait for crew to review
- If crew assigns back to you (revisions needed), resume work
- If crew closes bead or assigns to architect/polecats, you're done

